# Gematria Cipher Betting App — Build Guide

This document is the authoritative reference for AI agents maintaining the Gematria
Cipher Betting System. Read this before modifying any code.

---

## 1. Architecture Overview

### Stack

| Layer | Technology | Version |
|-------|-----------|---------|
| Framework | Next.js (App Router) | 16.2.1 |
| UI | React | 19.2.4 |
| Language | TypeScript | 5.x |
| Styling | Tailwind CSS v4 | 4.x |
| Database | Supabase (PostgreSQL + PostgREST) | 2.100.1 |
| AI | Anthropic Claude SDK | 0.80.0 |
| Charts | Recharts | 3.8.1 |
| Icons | lucide-react | 1.7.0 |
| Toasts | sonner | 2.0.7 |

### Path Alias

`@/` maps to `src/`. All imports use this alias. Example: `import { getTodayET } from '@/lib/date-utils'`.

### Dev Server

```
npm run dev
```

Runs on port 3000 by default. No custom port configuration.

### Critical Architectural Rules

1. **Dates**: ALWAYS use `getTodayET()` from `@/lib/date-utils`. NEVER use raw
   `new Date()` for calendar-date logic. The ET conversion prevents the UTC midnight
   rollover bug where games at 7 PM ET appear under the wrong date.

2. **Supabase clients**: `getSupabase()` for client-side reads (anon key).
   `getSupabaseAdmin()` for ALL server-side writes (service key). Using the anon
   client for writes will silently fail due to RLS policies.

3. **Request interception**: Next.js 16 uses `proxy.ts` (NOT `middleware.ts`).
   The proxy function is exported from `src/proxy.ts` and handles auth gating.

4. **API routes**: Every route must export `const dynamic = 'force-dynamic'`.
   Long-running routes (analyze) must export `const maxDuration = 300`.

5. **Shell**: The host OS is Windows/PowerShell. Use `;` not `&&` for chaining
   shell commands.

