### gematria.ts

Pure deterministic cipher engine. No AI, no network calls.

**Cipher tables (exported):**

| Constant | Mapping |
|----------|---------|
| `ORDINAL` | A=1, B=2, ... Z=26 |
| `REDUCTION` | A=1, B=2, ... I=9, J=1, K=2, ... R=9, S=1, ... Z=8 |
| `REV_ORDINAL` | A=26, B=25, ... Z=1 |
| `REV_REDUCTION` | A=8, B=7, ... I=9, J=8, ... R=9, S=8, ... Z=1 |

**Exported functions:**

| Function | Signature | Purpose |
|----------|-----------|---------|
| `calculateGematria` | `(text: string) => GematriaResult` | Compute all 4 cipher values for a string |
| `calculateDateNumerology` | `(date: Date) => DateNumerology` | Compute all 8 date methods |
| `getAllGematriaValues` | `(result: GematriaResult) => number[]` | Extract array of 4 cipher values |
| `getAllDateValues` | `(numerology: DateNumerology) => number[]` | Extract array of 8 date values |
| `findMatchingValues` | `(gematria, dateNums) => Match[]` | Find cipher-date value matches |

**Date numerology methods:**

| Method | Calculation | Example (4/8/2026) |
|--------|-------------|-------------------|
| `full` | month + day + first2OfYear + last2OfYear | 4 + 8 + 20 + 26 = 58 |
| `reducedYear` | month + day + digitSum(year) | 4 + 8 + 10 = 22 |
| `singleDigits` | digitSum(month) + digitSum(day) + digitSum(year) | 4 + 8 + 10 = 22 |
| `shortYear` | month + day + last2OfYear | 4 + 8 + 26 = 38 |
| `monthDay` | month + day | 4 + 8 = 12 |
| `rootNumber` | reduce singleDigits to one digit | 22 -> 4 |
| `calendarDay` | day of month (1-31) | 8 |
| `calendarMonth` | month number (1-12) | 4 |

Note: `calendarMonth` is excluded from auto-matching in `findMatchingValues` because
small integers produce excessive noise. It is available in the calculator UI.

