### sports-api.ts

Fetches game schedules and scores from ESPN and NHL public APIs.

**Base URLs:**
- ESPN: `https://site.api.espn.com/apis/site/v2/sports`
- NHL: `https://api-web.nhle.com/v1`

**Exports:**

| Function | Signature | Purpose |
|----------|-----------|---------|
| `fetchWithRetry` | `(url, retries=3, delayMs=1000) => Promise<Response>` | HTTP GET with retry + backoff on 429/5xx |
| `parseEspnCompetitorScore` | `(raw) => number` | Normalize ESPN score field (number, string, or `{value}` object) |
| `fetchNBAGames` | `(dateStr: string) => Promise<ESPNGame[]>` | NBA scoreboard for YYYYMMDD date |
| `fetchMLBGames` | `(dateStr: string) => Promise<ESPNGame[]>` | MLB scoreboard for YYYYMMDD date |
| `fetchNHLGames` | `(dateStr: string) => Promise<NHLGame[]>` | NHL schedule for YYYY-MM-DD date |
| `fetchNhlStandingsMap` | `(forceFresh?) => Promise<NhlStandingsByAbbrev>` | NHL W-L-OTL standings (10-min cache) |
| `buildNhlStandingsByAbbrev` | `(data) => NhlStandingsByAbbrev` | Parse standings API response |

**CRITICAL date format difference:**
- ESPN uses `YYYYMMDD` (no dashes): `20260408`
- NHL uses `YYYY-MM-DD` (with dashes): `2026-04-08`
- The fetch functions handle this internally, but callers pass YYYY-MM-DD and
  `fetchNBAGames`/`fetchMLBGames` strip dashes.

**ESPN response shape:**
```
data.events[].competitions[0].competitors[] -> { homeAway, team.displayName, score, records[0].summary }
data.events[].competitions[0].venue -> { fullName, address.city, address.state }
data.events[].competitions[0].status -> { type.state ('pre'|'in'|'post'), period, displayClock }
```

**NHL response shape:**
```
data.gameWeek[].games[] -> { id, startTimeUTC, gameState, homeTeam, awayTeam, venue.default }
homeTeam/awayTeam -> { id, placeName.default, commonName.default, abbrev, score }
```

NHL `gameState` values: `FUT`, `PRE` -> 'pre'; `LIVE`, `CRIT` -> 'in'; `OFF`, `FINAL` -> 'post'

NHL standings are fetched separately from `api-web.nhle.com/v1/standings/now` because
the schedule endpoint no longer includes W-L-OTL records.

