## 8. External API Contracts

### ESPN NBA Scoreboard

```
GET https://site.api.espn.com/apis/site/v2/sports/basketball/nba/scoreboard?dates=YYYYMMDD
```

Response parsing:
```
data.events[] -> each is a game
  .id -> game ID (string)
  .date -> ISO start time
  .competitions[0]
    .competitors[] -> { homeAway: 'home'|'away', team: { displayName, abbreviation, id }, score, records: [{ summary: 'W-L' }] }
    .venue -> { fullName, address: { city, state } }
    .status -> { type: { state: 'pre'|'in'|'post' }, period, displayClock }
```

### ESPN MLB Scoreboard

Same format as NBA at:
```
GET https://site.api.espn.com/apis/site/v2/sports/baseball/mlb/scoreboard?dates=YYYYMMDD
```

Additional: postponed/suspended games (`status.type.name` = `STATUS_POSTPONED` or
`STATUS_SUSPENDED`) are filtered out and return `null` (removed by `.filter(Boolean)`).

### NHL Schedule

```
GET https://api-web.nhle.com/v1/schedule/YYYY-MM-DD
```

Response parsing:
```
data.gameWeek[] -> { date: 'YYYY-MM-DD', games: [...] }
  games[].id -> game ID (number, used as string)
  games[].startTimeUTC -> ISO timestamp
  games[].gameState -> 'FUT'|'PRE'|'LIVE'|'CRIT'|'OFF'|'FINAL'
  games[].homeTeam / awayTeam -> { id, placeName.default, commonName.default, abbrev, score }
  games[].venue.default -> arena name
```

### NHL Standings

```
GET https://api-web.nhle.com/v1/standings/now
```

Response parsing:
```
data.standings[] -> { teamAbbrev.default, wins, losses, otLosses }
```

Cached for 10 minutes in `nhlStandingsCache`.

### Polymarket Gamma Events

```
GET https://gamma-api.polymarket.com/events?active=true&closed=false&limit=200&tag={tag}
```

Tags: `basketball`, `hockey`, `baseball`

Response: array of event objects, each with:
```
event.slug -> e.g. 'nba-sas-mil-2026-03-28'
event.title -> e.g. 'San Antonio Spurs vs Milwaukee Bucks'
event.markets[] -> [{ sportsMarketType, outcomePrices, outcomes, line, active, closed }]
```

`outcomePrices` can be a JSON string `'["0.54","0.46"]'` or a real array.
`outcomes` can also be a JSON string. Always parse defensively.

### Anthropic Claude Messages API

```typescript
const client = new Anthropic();
const response = await client.messages.create({
  model: settings.model,   // e.g. 'claude-sonnet-4-20250514'
  max_tokens: 2048,
  system: systemMessage,
  messages: [{ role: 'user', content: userMessage }],
});
const text = response.content.find(b => b.type === 'text')?.text;
```

Requires `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` environment variable.

