## 10. Claude Agent Protocol

### System Message Construction

The system message is built from three parts concatenated with `\n\n`:
1. `settings.system_prompt` — user-written instructions
2. `settings.bet_rules` — user-written constraints
3. Hard-coded JSON format instructions (response schema)

### User Message Structure

```
=== GAME ===
{away_team} @ {home_team}
League: {league} | Date: {game_date}
Venue: {venue}
Records: Home {record} | Away {record}
Moon: {illumination}% illumination {(FULL MOON) if applicable}

=== DATE NUMEROLOGY ===
Full: {full} | Reduced Year: {reducedYear} | Single Digits: {singleDigits}
Short Year: {shortYear} | Month+Day: {monthDay}
Root Number: {rootNumber} | Calendar Day: {calendarDay} | Calendar Month: {calendarMonth}

=== HOME TEAM CIPHERS ({home_team}) ===
  City ({city}): Ord {n} | Red {n} | RevOrd {n} | RevRed {n}
  Team ({teamName}): Ord {n} | Red {n} | RevOrd {n} | RevRed {n}
  Full ({fullName}): Ord {n} | Red {n} | RevOrd {n} | RevRed {n}
  {Stars, Goalie, Coach if present}

=== HOME TEAM ALIGNMENTS ===
  {bullet list of alignments with type, cipher, value, date method}

=== AWAY TEAM CIPHERS / ALIGNMENTS ===
  {same format}

=== GEMATRIA SUMMARY ===
Lock Type: {TRIPLE LOCK|DOUBLE LOCK|SINGLE LOCK|SKIP}
Home Alignments: {count}
Away Alignments: {count}
Confidence: {pct}%
Favored Side: {home|away|Neither}

=== ODDS ===
Moneyline: Home +/-{n} / Away +/-{n}
Implied: Home {pct}% / Away {pct}%
Spread: {line}
O/U: {line} (Over +/-{n}) (Under +/-{n})
```

### Expected Response Format

Claude must return a JSON array of TradeDecision objects:
```json
[{
  "action": "bet",
  "betType": "moneyline",
  "pick": "Boston Celtics",
  "pickedSide": "home",
  "odds": -150,
  "impliedProbability": 0.6,
  "modelProbability": 0.68,
  "ev": 0.13,
  "units": 3,
  "confidence": 75,
  "reasoning": "Triple lock with strong city alignment..."
}]
```

For a skip: `[{ "action": "skip", ... }]`

