## 18. Request Flow Diagrams

### Fetch + Analyze + Settle Pipeline

```
User clicks "Fetch Games"
  -> POST /api/fetch-games
    -> fetchNBAGames(today) + fetchNHLGames(today) + fetchMLBGames(today) [parallel]
    -> upsert to games table
    -> fetchPolymarketOdds('NBA') + ('NHL') + ('MLB') [parallel]
    -> match odds to games, update polymarket_odds JSONB

User clicks "Analyze & Bet"
  -> POST /api/analyze (SSE stream)
    -> load gematria_settings
    -> query games where game_date=today AND analyzed=false
    -> for each game:
      -> analyzeGame() (deterministic cipher engine)
      -> build Claude prompt
      -> call Claude API
      -> parse JSON response
      -> if auto-bet enabled for lock type + confidence >= min:
        -> insert paper_trades
        -> deduct from balance
      -> mark game analyzed=true
    -> upsert bankroll_ledger

User clicks "Settle Bets"
  -> POST /api/settle
    -> query paper_trades where result='pending' (join games)
    -> for each unique game_date:
      -> fetch fresh scores from ESPN/NHL/MLB
    -> for each trade with final game:
      -> determineTradeResult(trade, homeScore, awayScore)
      -> profitLossForSettledTrade(trade, result)
      -> update paper_trades (result, profit_loss, settled_at)
    -> upsert bankroll_ledger
```

### Auth Flow

```
User visits any page
  -> proxy.ts intercepts
  -> checks gematria-session cookie
  -> if missing/invalid: redirect to /login (pages) or 401 (API)

User submits password on /login
  -> POST /api/auth/login
  -> compare password to APP_PASSWORD env
  -> if match: create HMAC token, set cookie, return 200
  -> client redirects to /
```
